com.ibm.team.scm.common.dto

Interface IOrphanDescriptor


  • public interface IOrphanDescriptor
    Describes the specific item (and current or potential parent) which would have become an orphan in the configuration if the operation succeeded.
    Since:
    0.6

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      IVersionableHandle getItemOrphaned()
      Return the item which would be missing a parent in the configuration if the operation succeeded.
      IFolderHandle getParent()
      Return the parent that the item is looking for in the configuration.

    • Method Detail

      • getItemOrphaned

        IVersionableHandle getItemOrphaned()
        Return the item which would be missing a parent in the configuration if the operation succeeded.
        Returns:
        the item orphaned, never null

      • getParent

        IFolderHandle getParent()
        Return the parent that the item is looking for in the configuration.
        Returns:
        the parent which has gone missing. may be null if that is how the client specified the state to be saved to have no parent; otherwise, will not be null. This item may not have ever existed in the repository.
